{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LxNzbSdidkdNp3yQBJhbpN","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ddf6778-e52b-4fac-a106-840f4425a12e","uuid":"b594fb32-65e7-4132-be67-f8420c984cde","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:42:30.042Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.\n- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.\n- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.\n- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":17,"newStart":1,"newLines":14,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27"," ","-### Session 31 — state corruption fix #15, no-op (2026-03-27T19:33Z)","+### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)"," ","-- **State corruption fix #15**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review`, phantom `1-1-foo` present, counts 75/70.","-- `registerStory` guard from session 22 is NOT in dist/ — tree-shaken by tsup. The `startsWith(\"{\")` guard and `updateStoryStatus` phantom rejection ARE in dist/.","-- The phantom `1-1-foo` persists because it was already in sprint-state.json before the fix was deployed. The fix prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean up existing ones.","-- Ralph likely reads state at process start, runs an iteration, and writes the stale state back — overwriting our manual fixes.","-- Fixed: removed phantom, restored all 4 stories to `done`, counts to 74/74.","-- All 74 stories done. No actionable work. Sprint complete.","-- **Root cause still active**: ralph's process lifetime spans multiple sessions. It reads state once, and if the state was corrupt when it started, it keeps writing corrupt state. The fix needs to be: either ralph re-reads state from disk before each write, or the phantom is cleaned up at ralph startup.","+- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.","+- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.","+- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.","+- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state."," "," ## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: ~15","-- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 1, Bash: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1","-- Files read: 5 unique, 7 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of tree-shaking issue","+- Total tool calls: ~12","+- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4","+- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads","+- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue"]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 31 — state corruption fix #15, no-op (2026-03-27T19:33Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #15**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review`, phantom `1-1-foo` present, counts 75/70.\n- `registerStory` guard from session 22 is NOT in dist/ — tree-shaken by tsup. The `startsWith(\"{\")` guard and `updateStoryStatus` phantom rejection ARE in dist/.\n- The phantom `1-1-foo` persists because it was already in sprint-state.json before the fix was deployed. The fix prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean up existing ones.\n- Ralph likely reads state at process start, runs an iteration, and writes the stale state back — overwriting our manual fixes.\n- Fixed: removed phantom, restored all 4 stories to `done`, counts to 74/74.\n- All 74 stories done. No actionable work. Sprint complete.\n- **Root cause still active**: ralph's process lifetime spans multiple sessions. It reads state once, and if the state was corrupt when it started, it keeps writing corrupt state. The fix needs to be: either ralph re-reads state from disk before each write, or the phantom is cleaned up at ralph startup.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~15\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 1, Bash: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Files read: 5 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of tree-shaking issue\n"}}
